<h1 class=3D"center">Circle Sector and Segment</h1>=20


<p class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images=
/circle-slices.svg" alt=3D"circle sector segment" height=3D"195" width=3D"1=
95"></p>=20


<h2>Slices</h2>=20

<p>There are two main "slices" of a <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/g=
eometry/circle.html">circle</a>:</p>=20
<ul class=3D"disc">=20
	<li>A <b>sector</b> is like a slice of pizza, with a radius on two sides</=
li>=20
	<li>A <b>segment</b> is the part of a circle cut off by a "chord" (a line =
connecting two points on the circle)</li>

</ul>=20


<h2>Try Them!</h2>=20

<div class=3D"simple">

	<table style=3D"border: 0; margin:auto;">
		<tbody><tr style=3D"text-align:center;">
			<th scope=3D"col">Sector</th>
			<th scope=3D"col">Segment</th>
		</tr>
		<tr>
			<td>=20

<iframe width=3D"265" height=3D"275" scrolling=3D"no" title=3D"JavaScript A=
nimation" style=3D"display: block; margin: auto; border: none; background-c=
olor: transparent; overflow: hidden; transition: 0.6s ease-in-out; max-widt=
h: 100%;"></iframe><div class=3D"script" style=3D"width: 265px; height: 275=
px; display: none;">images/circle-prop.js?mode=3Dsector</div></td>
			<td>=20

<iframe width=3D"100%" height=3D"280px" scrolling=3D"no" title=3D"JavaScrip=
t Animation" style=3D"display: block; margin: auto; border: none; backgroun=
d-color: transparent; overflow: hidden; transition: 0.6s ease-in-out; max-w=
idth: 100%;"></iframe><div class=3D"script" style=3D"width: 265px; height: =
275px; display: none;">images/circle-prop.js?mode=3Dsegment</div></td>
		</tr>
	</tbody></table>=20
</div>=20


<h2>Area of a Sector</h2>=20

<div class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/images/fracti=
ons/pizza-slice.jpg" alt=3D"slice of pizza" height=3D"130" width=3D"200"></=
div>
<p>We can work out the Area of a Sector by comparing its angle to the angle=
 of a full circle.</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><i>Note: we are using <a href=3D"https://www.mathsisfun=
.com/geometry/radians.html">radians</a> for the angles.</i></p>=20
<div style=3D"clear: both;"></div>

<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/=
circle-sector-area.svg" alt=3D"circular sector area" height=3D"245" width=
=3D"410"></p>=20
<p>This is the reasoning:</p>=20
<div class=3D"two"> <span class=3D"lt">A circle has an angle of 2<span clas=
s=3D"times">=CF=80</span> and an Area of:</span><span class=3D"rt"><span cl=
ass=3D"times">=CF=80</span>r<sup>2</sup></span>
<span class=3D"lt">A Sector has an angle of <span class=3D"times">=CE=B8</s=
pan> <b>instead of</b> 2<span class=3D"times">=CF=80</span> so its Area is =
: </span><span class=3D"rt"><span class=3D"intbl"><em><span class=3D"times"=
>=CE=B8</span></em><strong>2<span class=3D"times">=CF=80</span></strong></s=
pan> =C3=97<span class=3D"times"> =CF=80</span>r<sup>2</sup></span>
<span class=3D"lt">Which can be simplified to:</span><span class=3D"rt"><sp=
an class=3D"intbl"><em><span class=3D"times">=CE=B8</span></em><strong>2</s=
trong></span> =C3=97 r<sup>2</sup></span>
</div>
<div class=3D"gap"></div>
<p class=3D"center large">Area of Sector <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"intbl"=
><em>=CE=B8</em><strong>2</strong></span> =C3=97 r<sup>2</sup>   <i>(when =
=CE=B8 is in radians)</i></p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">Area of Sector <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"intbl"=
><em>=CE=B8 =C3=97 <span class=3D"times">=CF=80</span></em><strong>360</str=
ong></span> =C3=97 r<sup>2</sup>   <i>(when =CE=B8 is in degrees)</i></p>=
=20


<h2>Area of Segment</h2>=20

<div class=3D"floatRt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/imag=
es/rainbow.jpg" alt=3D"rainbow forma a segment" height=3D"93" width=3D"250"=
></div>
<p>The Area of a Segment is the area of a sector minus the triangular piece=
 shaded blue below:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images/=
circle-segment-area.svg" alt=3D"circular segment area" height=3D"217" width=
=3D"224"></p>=20
<p>There is a lengthy reason, but the result is a slight modification of th=
e Sector formula:</p>=20
<div style=3D"clear:both"></div>

<p class=3D"center large">Area of Segment <em>=3D</em> <span class=3D"intbl=
"><em>=CE=B8 =E2=88=92 sin(=CE=B8)</em><strong>2</strong></span> =C3=97 r<s=
up>2</sup>   <i>(when =CE=B8 is in radians)</i></p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">Area of Segment <em>=3D</em> ( <span class=3D"int=
bl"><em>=CE=B8 =C3=97 <span class=3D"times">=CF=80</span></em><strong>360</=
strong></span> =E2=88=92 <span class=3D"intbl"><em>sin(=CE=B8)</em><strong>=
2</strong></span>) =C3=97 r<sup>2</sup>   <i>(when =CE=B8 is in degrees)</i=
></p>=20
<div class=3D"gap"></div>
<p class=3D"floatLt"><img src=3D"https://www.mathsisfun.com/geometry/images=
/circle-arc-length.svg" alt=3D"circular sector arc length" height=3D"226" w=
idth=3D"199"></p>=20


<h2>Arc Length</h2>=20

<p>The arc length (of a <b>Sector or Segment</b>) is:</p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">L <em>=3D</em> =CE=B8 =C3=97 r   <i>(when =CE=B8 =
is in radians)</i></p>=20
<p class=3D"center large">L <em>=3D</em> =CE=B8 =C3=97 <span class=3D"intbl=
"><em><span class=3D"times">=CF=80</span></em><strong>180</strong></span> =
=C3=97 r   <i>(when =CE=B8 is in degrees)</i></p>=20
<div class=3D"gap"></div>

<iframe width=3D"798" height=3D"265" scrolling=3D"no" title=3D"JavaScript A=
nimation" style=3D"display: block; margin: auto; border: none; background-c=
olor: transparent; overflow: hidden; transition: 0.6s ease-in-out; max-widt=
h: 100%;"></iframe><div class=3D"script" style=3D"height: 265px; display: n=
one;">images/circle-prop.js?mode=3Darclen</div>

